Here's the standard approach:

### 1. Define each theme as a `ResourceDictionary`

```xml
<!-- Themes/LightTheme.xaml -->
<ResourceDictionary xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
                    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml">
    <Color x:Key="PageBackground">#FFFFFF</Color>
    <Color x:Key="PrimaryText">#1A1A1A</Color>
    <Color x:Key="Accent">#0078D4</Color>
</ResourceDictionary>
```

Create matching `DarkTheme.xaml` and `HighContrastTheme.xaml` with the same keys but different values.

### 2. Load a default theme in `App.xaml`

```xml
<Application.Resources>
    <ResourceDictionary>
        <ResourceDictionary.MergedDictionaries>
            <local:LightTheme />
        </ResourceDictionary.MergedDictionaries>
    </ResourceDictionary>
</Application.Resources>
```

### 3. Create a theme-switching helper

```csharp
public static class ThemeManager
{
    public static void ApplyTheme(string theme)
    {
        var mergedDicts = Application.Current!.Resources.MergedDictionaries;
        mergedDicts.Clear();

        mergedDicts.Add(theme switch
        {
            "Dark"         => new DarkTheme(),
            "HighContrast"  => new HighContrastTheme(),
            _               => new LightTheme(),
        });

        // Persist the choice
        Preferences.Set("AppTheme", theme);
    }
}
```

### 4. Call it from your settings page

```csharp
// In your SettingsPage or ViewModel
ThemeManager.ApplyTheme("Dark");
```

### 5. Restore on startup in `App.xaml.cs`

```csharp
public App()
{
    InitializeComponent();
    ThemeManager.ApplyTheme(Preferences.Get("AppTheme", "Light"));
}
```

### Key points

- **Use `DynamicResource`** (not `StaticResource`) in all XAML bindings so values update live when dictionaries swap:
  ```xml
  <Label TextColor="{DynamicResource PrimaryText}" />
  ```
- **Keep identical keys** across all three dictionaries — a missing key will silently fall back or break.
- `MergedDictionaries.Clear()` + `Add()` triggers `DynamicResource` rebinding immediately, so the UI updates without restarting the app.
